      • getOptionDelegates

        public ReleasableIterator<? extends IOptionHolder> getOptionDelegates()
        Description copied from interface: IOptionHolder
        Iterates over option holders in order in of lookup precedence.

        This should be the first object returned by the iterator.

        The default implementation provided by AbstractOptionHolder returns a OptionParentIterator instance, which simply walks up the chain of option parents.

        Specified by:
        getOptionDelegates in interface IOptionHolder

      • getOptionParent

        @Nullable
public IOptionHolder getOptionParent()
        Description copied from interface: IOptionHolder
        The "parent" of this option holder to which option lookup will be delegated for option keys that are not set on this object. Used by IOptionHolder.getOption(IOptionKey).

        Implementors should ensure that chain of parents is not circular!

        Specified by:
        getOptionParent in interface IOptionHolder
        Returns:
        the parent object or null if there is none.

      • getOptionOrDefault

        public <T extends java.io.Serializable> T getOptionOrDefault(IOptionKey<T> key)
        Description copied from interface: IOptionHolder
        Returns value of option with given key or else its default value.

        The same as IOptionHolder.getOption(com.analog.lyric.options.IOptionKey<T>) but returns the key's defaultValue instead of null if option is not set.

        Specified by:
        getOptionOrDefault in interface IOptionHolder

      • getOption

        @Nullable
public <T extends java.io.Serializable> T getOption(IOptionKey<T> key)
        Description copied from interface: IOptionHolder
        Returns value of option with given key if set, else null.

        Returns the value of the first option setting found in this object or in its list of delegates. Specifically it invokes IOptionHolder.getLocalOption(com.analog.lyric.options.IOptionKey<T>) on each object in IOptionHolder.getOptionDelegates() and returns the first non-null result.

        Specified by:
        getOption in interface IOptionHolder
        Parameters:
        key - is a non-null option key.

      • getOptionAndSource

        @Nullable
public <T extends java.io.Serializable> T getOptionAndSource(IOptionKey<T> key,
                                                             @Nullable
                                                             IOptionHolder[] source)
        Returns value and source of option with given key if set, else null.

        Parameters:
        key - is a non-null option key.
        source - if non-null with length at least one, the first element will be set to the object whose local option setting produced the return value. Nothing will be written if this method returns null.
        Since:
        0.07
        See Also:

      • getOptionUptoDepth

        @Nullable
public <T extends java.io.Serializable> T getOptionUptoDepth(IOptionKey<T> key,
                                                             int maxDepth,
                                                             int[] depthReference)
        Returns value and source of option with up to specified depth in delegation chain.

        Parameters:
        key - is a non-null option key.
        maxDepth - is the maximum number of option delegates to examine. If zero, then only the current object will be examined.
        depthReference - is a non-empty array whose first entry will be set to the depth of the option setting in the delegation chain or else set to Integer.MAX_VALUE if no option setting was found.
        Returns:
        option value set for given key. Will be null if option is not set within the first 1 + maxDepth delegates.
        Since:
        0.07
